OL,3,CMum heard 'last gurgling breaths' of
OL,4,Ccar-loving son as life support turned
OL,5,Coff
OL,7,FA grieving mum has recalled the moment
OL,8,Fher son's life support machine was
OL,9,Fturned off, after he was involved in a
OL,10,Fcar crash late at night, on the way
OL,11,Fhome from a car meet.
OL,13,FDr Steph Alger's son Etienne, known as
OL,14,FJustin, was 18 when he lost control of
OL,15,Fhis car. He was driving at 66mph,
OL,16,Fwhich was only a little over the legal
OL,17,Flimit, but the road was wet, he took a
OL,18,Fcorner too quickly, and he had a nail
OL,19,Fin his tyre.
