OL,3,CMum heard 'last gurgling breaths' of
OL,4,Ccar-loving son as life support turned
OL,5,Coff
OL,7,F"Watching my son slip away slowly,
OL,8,Fhearing his raspy breath fade away, it
OL,9,Fwas the longest two hours of my entire
OL,10,Flife. I knew what was going to happen,
OL,11,Fbut I just tried to make the most of
OL,12,Fevery moment of time we had with him.
OL,13,FBut he was gone.
OL,15,F"It sounds really morbid that you want
OL,16,Fto hear the last gurgling breaths of
OL,17,Fyour child, but it's like you want to
OL,18,Ftake ownership, you want to own every
OL,19,Flast minute of them.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/11
