OL,3,CMum heard 'last gurgling breaths' of
OL,4,Ccar-loving son as life support turned
OL,5,Coff
OL,7,F"I tried to bathe my son and attempted
OL,8,Fto get the grit out of his hands and
OL,9,Fof his face. But, he smelt like he was
OL,10,Fdying. There is an overwhelming sort
OL,11,Fof acidic smell to death that I
OL,12,Frecognised as a sign that he was gone."
OL,14,FDr Alger's life stopped from that
OL,15,Fmoment.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/11
